Fixed import errors and updated to support python 3- Imported queue as queue to avoid import error- Enabled backward compatible flask serverUpdated main.pyRemoved useless importMade the npm build more cleanRemoved depricated use of open() + made port flexibleRemoved the warning to get a clean build:  DeprecationWarning: `open()` is deprecated in mongoose >= 4.11.0 by declaring the boolean value of Mongoclient as true.What I personally encountered... I was running another server on port 3000, Thus when I was setting up Dronesym, I got an error of port already being in use, So I made a global variable named port, and added string concatenation to console the running port into the terminal. If users already have port 3000 in use, then they could just change the value of variable in /dronesym-node/index.js.Added missing instruction of running mongodMost of the people including me forgot to run ```mongod``` in one terminal, and then execute ```mongorestore --db dronesym dronedb/dronesym```, So I've added an instruction step.Added latest and more supportive version of flaskAdded E2E tests for Login authorization 1. Checks URL redirection vulnerability (security purpose).2. Checks Server's availability.3. Checks Login authorization through admin's account.4. Checks the dashboard appearance on putting correct credentials.5. Logs out of admin's account 6. Checks Login authorization through admin's account.
